text: This used to be my absolute favorite place for french cuisine, prices were reasonable, food was great, atmosphere was classy & low-key, far less obnoxiously busy than nearby Bistro Campagne can be. Â In August of 2005 they changed their name to Cork, now they are apparently a wine bar, I've not visited their new incarnation which food-wise now serves only "small plates", sounds kinda like french tapas or dim sum??
Great place to get inexpensive French food. They have great service here and really great food. Everything here is no-fuss and its a wonderul place to go for a great, inexpensive meal.
